Customer emailed for explanation of why the claim was declined. I wrote:
My apologies for the lack of response to your previous email. 
Please allow me to explain the position of Canada General Warranty.
On September 9, 2022, Nick from Galaxy Motors contacted our office to initiate a claim. He explained that they had replaced the rear main oil seal several times but it continued to leak. They had determined that the seal kept failing due to excessive crankcase pressure. They had also determined that this excessive pressure was due to worn piston rings and cylinder walls.
Unfortunately, this warranty and any other warranty, does not cover worn rings and cylinder walls so, the claim was declined.
Under "Events That Are Not Covered By This Policy" section 20 states "any Vehicle damage due to wear and tear, corrosion, rust, or other gradual loss or reduction of function;" 
Worn cylinder  walls and piston rings fall under this exclusion.
I'm sorry we cannot be of assistance with this repair. I trust this explanation clarifies our position.

Sincerely,
